document_data.History:
On the spring of 1373 DR, Elowen came across Araluen, at the moment known as Ash, in [[Fullpoint]] after the village was attacked by [[blightspawned]] [[volodni]]. Together with the Gunggari Ulmarra and the priest Marrec, she managed to save Ash from her kidnappers.{{cite book/Lady of Poison|32|4}} Learning from Ususi that the [[Mucklestones]] were imperiled,{{cite book/Lady of Poison|53-54|6}} they headed there to check up on [[Briartan]]; there, they fought the [[Talontar blightlord]] [[Gameliel]] and rescued Briartan, who was his captive.{{cite book/Lady of Poison|85-86|10}}

Per Briartan's advice, they headed for [[Yeshelmaar]], where she gave a debriefing regarding the situation to the Circle of Leth.{{cite book/Lady of Poison|109|12}} After the group spoke with the Nentyarch, he bestowed [[Dymondheart]] on her, and bade her accompany Marrec and Ash, or Araluen, on their quest to confront the [[Rotting Man]].{{cite book/Lady of Poison|125-127|13}} However, when her fellow Nentyar hunter, Fallon, kidnapped Ash, they were forced to give chase before being able to complete their preparations.{{cite book/Lady of Poison|133|14}} They chased Fallon across the [[Celestial Nadir]], and were ambushed by [[Anammelech]] on exiting it.{{cite book/Lady of Poison|145|14}} After the second blightlord's defeat, they proceeded through thee tunnels of [[Under-Tharos]], and were pressed into a fight between two demons: the [[Queen Abiding]] and [[Eschar]].{{cite book/Lady of Poison|187|18}} Successfully prying off the Queen Abiding's command token from Eschar,{{cite book/Lady of Poison|236-238|25}} they emerged in the [[Rawlinswood]] close to [[Dun-Tharos]], where they soon came across a third blightlord, [[Damanda]]:{{cite book/Lady of Poison|253-254|27}} after the fight, they caught up with a dying Fallon and finally recovered Araluen.{{cite book/Lady of Poison|259|27}}

They challenged the [[Rotting Man]] soon after; during the fight, Elowen personally destroyed [[Damanda]].{{cite book/Lady of Poison|285-286|30}} After the Rotting Man ordered the Step-Daughter of Talona to fight them, Elowen was quickly knocked out by the rampaging abomination.{{cite book/Lady of Poison|290|30}} She survived the fight, however, and judged that she had made new friends during the quest.{{cite book/Lady of Poison|307|epilogue}}
